During the course, the student obtains experiences in the work environment by visiting different educational institutions and using job shadowing, and reflects the experience in the practice logbook. The obtained experiences enable the student to link his/her previous knowledge and skills with practical work and prepare for the practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to enable the student to attune to the circumstances of the chosen practice site and to prepare for the practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, the student: - has an overview of the characteristics of observed work environment  - has an overview of the characteristics of observed position; - is able to notice the relevant features of organisational processes and describe them.
